  "body": "To trigger the bug, use this hardhat config:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nclass Foo {\r\n  constructor(hre) {\r\n    this.hre = hre;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nextendEnvironment(hre => {\r\n  hre.foo = lazyObject(() => new Foo(hre))\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen start `hh console` and evaluate the `hre`. Note that if you are using node >= 12, then just typing \"hre\" in the console will trigger this bug.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure the problem is here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/d59ef54e108f3ab2891dd963f2f9913c073ab0f5/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/util/lazy.ts#L39-L42\r\n\r\nReplacing that function with `return \"\"` makes the problem go away. There's something in the intersection of `lazyObject`, the HRE and `util.inspect` that causes this.\r\n\r\nNotice that the snippet above is the minimal reproduction as far as I can tell. A simple cicrularity with `lazyObject` doesn't cause this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nextendEnvironment(hre => {\r\n  hre.foo = lazyObject(() => {\r\n    let foo = {}\r\n    foo.foo = foo;\r\n\r\n    return foo\r\n  })\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd a circularity with the hre but without `lazyObject` doesn't cause it either:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nextendEnvironment(hre => {\r\n  hre.foo = new Foo(hre)\r\n}\r\n```",
